  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a HarfBuzz color value using BGRA byte ordering.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`HBColor` wraps a `hb_color_t` value, which stores color channels as `0xBBGGRRAA`
(blue in the highest byte, alpha in the lowest byte). This differs from
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, which uses `0xAARRGGBB` (ARGB).

Use the named properties (`Red`, `Green`, `Blue`, `Alpha`) to read individual
channels, and the `HBColor(byte, byte, byte, byte)` constructor to create a
color from components without worrying about byte ordering.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from RGBA components
var color = new HBColor(red: 255, green: 128, blue: 0, alpha: 255);
Console.WriteLine($"R={color.Red} G={color.Green} B={color.Blue} A={color.Alpha}");

// Convert from SKColor
using SkiaSharp.HarfBuzz;
HBColor hb = SKColors.CornflowerBlue.ToHBColor();
```
]]></format></remarks>
